Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.44,0:00:04.04,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,But this is the goal of my journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.36,0:00:09.11,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,To reunite with my friend \Nwho departed ten years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.85,0:00:19.00,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Did you figure out where Gorilla went?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.77,0:00:22.11,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Tür.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.51,0:00:25.83,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,It's a trading city in the middle \Nof the northern lands.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.83,0:00:28.12,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That's a long ways east from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.51,0:00:31.38,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's in the opposite \Ndirection from Äußerst.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.36,0:00:33.45,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.57,0:00:47.69,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren, I came on this journey \Nto chase after Gorilla.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.18,0:00:49.41,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.76,0:00:53.62,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,The sun's about to set.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.62,0:00:56.16,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Can't we wait until tomorrow \Nto make a decision?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.56,0:01:01.23,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I asked the village to lend us a cabin.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.23,0:01:03.09,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,They said we can use it \Nhowever we want.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.64,0:01:04.84,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.06,0:01:20.98,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,You're there like the wind
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.98,0:01:25.60,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Closing your eyes at sunset
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.60,0:01:31.25,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what's on your mind
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.52,0:01:36.57,Signs,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(857,1)\blur0.25\fs35\fnGeorgia\fsp3.9\c&HFFFE65&\pos(328,254)\clip(109,253,547,294)\t(3943,4986,\clip(109,253,110,294))}Beyond Journey's End
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.97,0:01:39.95,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,With your eyelids open
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.95,0:01:44.53,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Your eyes shone like glass
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.53,0:01:51.30,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,It faintly smelled like a sunny day
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.23,0:02:02.43,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Clear up the sky, let flowers bloom
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.43,0:02:06.63,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Bloom and blame it on the sunny sky
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.63,0:02:11.02,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even the rain, when it stops
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.02,0:02:16.02,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Will make you shine in the sunlight
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.02,0:02:21.42,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Calm the stirring sounds in my heart
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.42,0:02:25.46,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,We go like the sunny wind
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.46,0:02:29.87,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Go on and fly over that cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.87,0:02:34.70,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Further and further away
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.01,0:02:41.01,Signs_EpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.2\c&HFAFFF7&\pos(414,270.5)}Episode 17: Take Care
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.73,0:02:58.73,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,I got firewood.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.73,0:03:02.19,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I bought ingredients for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.06,0:03:06.72,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,My hands are freezing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.72,0:03:09.43,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It has gotten rather cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.04,0:03:11.63,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.63,0:03:14.35,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, this might be a new record.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.16,0:03:19.38,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Let me see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.06,0:03:22.63,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. They're really cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.63,0:03:23.64,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.96,0:03:30.26,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.66,0:03:32.39,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this a new record?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.39,0:03:34.34,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. They're freezing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.34,0:03:35.71,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.17,0:03:43.77,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It's snowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.30,0:03:47.40,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Will we need to wait \Nfor winter to pass again?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.87,0:03:51.67,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We won't be crossing any \Nsteep mountains this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.01,0:03:55.28,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Unless there's a serious blizzard, \Nwe'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.95,0:04:02.40,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It's blizzarding.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.40,0:04:03.52,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,It sure is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.52,0:04:04.55,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.40,0:04:08.59,Default,CABIN OWNER,0000,0000,0000,,In this region, cold waves \Nlast an entire month.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.59,0:04:10.93,Default,CABIN OWNER,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't recommend venturing far.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.43,0:04:14.71,Default,CABIN OWNER,0000,0000,0000,,You can keep using the cabin for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.43,0:04:21.13,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want to do, Sein? \NShould we leave?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.13,0:04:23.57,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Do you even need to ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.57,0:04:26.33,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,So we're stuck here until \Nthe cold wave passes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.33,0:04:27.70,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,That's what it sounds like.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.45,0:04:31.59,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,But there are bars and shops here, at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.59,0:04:33.51,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,This cabin's nice and large, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.51,0:04:36.67,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's a lot better than the mountain cabin \Nwe stayed in before.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.70,0:04:43.65,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,And most importantly, there's a magic shop \Nin this village run by a shady old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.43,0:04:49.45,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,In my experience, shops like those \Ntend to have legendary-level spells.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.62,0:04:53.57,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Getting to take my time \Nexploring it is a big win.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.10,0:04:56.53,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Legendary-level spells?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.53,0:04:58.68,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,What kinds have you encountered so far?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.19,0:05:05.53,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,A spell to get rid of mold \Nand a spell to remove tough oil stains.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.33,0:05:07.68,Flashback,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.58,0:05:12.84,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Those spells are so convenient, \Nthey changed my world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.84,0:05:15.29,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,They sound like a grandma's household wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.92,0:05:18.56,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, the only thing \Nwe can do now is wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.56,0:05:22.64,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We'll die if we underestimate \Nthe winters of the northern lands.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.18,0:05:28.54,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Stark {\i1}did{\i0} nearly die \Nin the Schwer Mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.54,0:05:31.34,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm from the northern lands.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.34,0:05:32.94,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,I know that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.37,0:05:39.91,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, sounds like we'll be staying \Ntogether for a while longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.20,0:06:11.75,Default,CABIN OWNER,0000,0000,0000,,The cold wave should be ending soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.08,0:06:15.25,Default,CABIN OWNER,0000,0000,0000,,It won't be long before you adventurers \Ncan finally continue on your journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.25,0:06:17.78,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.28,0:06:21.99,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Wait. Didn't we spend most of our time apart?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.49,0:06:24.48,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Sein.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.54,0:06:27.12,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have a minute?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.12,0:06:29.17,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Frieren?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.17,0:06:31.61,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,You don't often come to the tavern.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.21,0:06:36.06,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Stark and Fern are acting strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.06,0:06:39.42,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I think they're fighting. \NCould you mediate?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.70,0:06:43.80,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, but why are you asking me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.80,0:06:46.68,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Because mediating is a priest's job.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.51,0:06:48.64,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.46,0:06:57.42,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,What a sorry state of affairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.98,0:07:00.36,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,What happened here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.68,0:07:02.64,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It's Mr. Stark's fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.20,0:07:06.36,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it's all my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.06,0:07:09.08,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,We won't get anywhere like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.89,0:07:14.57,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Join me in the other room, one at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.77,0:07:27.67,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,So, what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.48,0:07:31.27,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Remember how Fern touched my cheek
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.27,0:07:34.52,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,with her cold hands when we \Nfirst arrived at the cabin?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.52,0:07:36.70,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.78,0:07:40.32,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Today, when I paid her back in kind,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.83,0:07:43.66,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,she got upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.66,0:07:45.06,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,What are you, a child?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.51,0:07:51.97,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Of course girls don't like it when \Nyou put your hands on their face.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.06,0:07:55.44,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay with leaving \Nthings the way they are?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.44,0:07:57.74,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to make up with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.20,0:08:03.07,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Stark. Unlike me, you're good at heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.07,0:08:05.24,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Be honest, and tell her how you feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.67,0:08:09.84,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to make up, \Nthen you have to tell her that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.15,0:08:13.21,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren won't mediate for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.23,0:08:19.05,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I know. I'll apologize to Fern.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.20,0:08:23.44,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Stark feels bad about what he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.76,0:08:27.76,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,He's just a kid. He didn't mean any harm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.76,0:08:32.32,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I know. I'm being stubborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.32,0:08:33.76,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to apologize to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.65,0:08:37.27,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It was my fault to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.71,0:08:40.25,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mind that he touched me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.75,0:08:46.06,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It's just... the arm he used to \Nrestrain my shoulder was so strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.15,0:08:51.30,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It scared me a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.42,0:08:55.39,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Do you not like Stark?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.01,0:08:58.46,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you ask that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.46,0:08:59.92,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Is that how it seems to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.52,0:09:04.66,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Then tell him you were scared and make up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.57,0:09:08.41,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Be gentler.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.41,0:09:09.86,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.55,0:09:16.68,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Just start dating already!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.84,0:09:23.20,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure what happened, \Nbut I think you're trying really hard, Sein.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.80,0:09:26.59,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for the help.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.51,0:09:33.61,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren, you're the only one \Nwho praises me like I'm a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.61,0:09:35.50,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,But you {\i1}are{\i0} a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.75,0:09:39.25,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it's not so bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.29,0:09:45.51,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,You know, I've been wondering.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.46,0:09:49.41,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you trouble yourself with me,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.41,0:09:52.56,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,like when you invited me to travel with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.99,0:09:57.51,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it really is a dislike of my own kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.07,0:10:00.75,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,The way you refused to go on an adventure
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.75,0:10:04.67,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,reminded me of myself before \NI left to defeat the Demon King.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.67,0:10:05.98,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It made me angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.38,0:10:10.55,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't explain why you \Nconcern yourself with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.55,0:10:15.84,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I think I wanted to give you a reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.40,0:10:17.82,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.25,0:10:23.55,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's what Himmel the Hero would've done.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.05,0:10:27.97,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Take my hand, Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.13,0:10:32.06,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be your reason to go on a journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.69,0:10:41.05,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,They gave me the courage to travel
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.05,0:10:44.17,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,and taught me the joy \Nof spending time with friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.13,0:10:47.57,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Sein?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.57,0:10:49.20,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Haven't you had fun?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.99,0:10:52.99,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.71,0:10:55.64,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,This has been a lot of fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.63,0:11:11.59,Flashback,YOUNG GORILLA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to become \Nan unforgettable hero like Himmel.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.99,0:11:15.99,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm talking about the present, Sein.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.46,0:11:21.49,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,So I decided to trust her words.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.02,0:11:26.34,Flashback,STUBBORN,0000,0000,0000,,Gorilla talked about you a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.34,0:11:31.82,Flashback,STUBBORN,0000,0000,0000,,He said the two of you would become heroes \Nwhose names would be remembered forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.30,0:11:58.93,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,I've decided to go after Gorilla.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.47,0:12:01.92,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,I won't live with regrets anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.65,0:12:04.13,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.03,0:12:06.52,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Take care, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.56,0:12:10.45,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,See you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.88,0:12:14.00,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.24,0:12:25.08,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that was a quick goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.08,0:12:28.11,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike you two, Sein is an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.63,0:12:30.34,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure he'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.89,0:12:51.87,Default,SEIN,0000,0000,0000,,It's so quiet traveling alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.00,0:13:03.01,Signs_BText,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.2\pos(588.5,16)}29 years after the death of Himmel the Hero,\Nin the Offen mountain range, located in the northern lands
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.13,0:13:16.01,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.39,0:13:19.51,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,That's unusual. They're still asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.16,0:13:22.35,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,We've been walking a lot recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.35,0:13:23.90,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe they're tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.34,0:13:40.84,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Good enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.20,0:13:46.76,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, breakfast is ready. Get up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.73,0:13:50.74,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Fern?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.05,0:13:57.34,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren, wake up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.45,0:14:00.74,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Just twelve more hours...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.74,0:14:03.23,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You can't sleep that long.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.65,0:14:05.99,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, Fern doesn't look well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.86,0:14:11.66,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.75,0:14:20.42,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.19,0:14:24.61,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You've got a fever.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.24,0:14:27.34,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You need to keep warm and rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.67,0:14:31.72,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.24,0:14:38.38,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? That's odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.38,0:14:39.90,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I brought water.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.65,0:14:41.73,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.73,0:14:43.32,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.32,0:14:47.71,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Sein left us some notes on medicinal herbs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.71,0:14:49.62,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Sein did, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.62,0:14:54.20,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I can use magic to identify her illness \Nand figure out which herbs to use.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.62,0:14:58.39,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,But I thought identifying illnesses \Nwas magic of the Goddess.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.39,0:15:02.16,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you say only the owner \Nof a holy scripture could cast it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.49,0:15:05.25,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I've got a holy scripture.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.25,0:15:05.88,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.43,0:15:12.46,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You're using it as a pot stand!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.54,0:15:20.12,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not cut out to be a priest, \Nbut even I can identify simple illnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.61,0:15:22.93,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I can't identify complex ones, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.93,0:15:24.30,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You sure you're okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.10,0:15:28.70,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It's just a cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.16,0:15:32.75,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Which of the applicable herbs \Nare found in this region?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.60,0:15:35.94,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.94,0:15:39.99,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,there's a place nearby where I once \Ngathered herbs with Himmel and the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.94,0:15:44.31,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,For now, let's head someplace \Nwhere we can get out of the cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.89,0:15:46.15,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.73,0:15:58.64,Default,VILLAGER,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.20,0:16:08.64,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You're a lifesaver.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.89,0:16:12.41,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think anyone lived \Nthis deep in the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.41,0:16:15.42,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,There was a whole village here \Nwhen I stopped by before.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.42,0:16:18.11,Default,VILLAGER,0000,0000,0000,,That was decades ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.54,0:16:23.33,Default,VILLAGER,0000,0000,0000,,It was a prestigious village \Nonce visited by the hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.81,0:16:26.58,Default,VILLAGER,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, make yourselves at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.32,0:16:28.47,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.17,0:16:33.01,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, isn't there an icicle \Ncherry blossom tree near here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.01,0:16:35.59,Default,VILLAGER,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, north of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.07,0:16:38.90,Default,VILLAGER,0000,0000,0000,,It's a bit difficult to get there, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.39,0:16:40.63,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.05,0:16:43.22,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I've been here before.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.09,0:16:47.81,Default,VILLAGER,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'll be working.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.44,0:16:51.93,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Wait here, Fern.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.41,0:16:54.62,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We'll gather the ingredients \Nwe need for your medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.12,0:16:57.93,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You've been holding her hand \Nsince we arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.46,0:17:00.15,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Because she seems to be in pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.43,0:17:05.22,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,When Fern has a cold, \Nholding her hand makes her feel better.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.74,0:17:07.88,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,She's been that way since she was a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.60,0:17:12.91,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.74,0:17:17.67,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren, you're embarrassing me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.46,0:17:19.68,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.28,0:17:23.98,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't treat me like a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.03,0:17:29.68,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I see. You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.46,0:17:36.69,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,In two years, she'll be a full-grown adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.77,0:17:41.27,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't long ago that \Nshe only came up to here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.79,0:17:44.89,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I was way taller than her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.89,0:17:46.63,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,But in the blink of an eye, she grew up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.25,0:17:51.38,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,In my mind, Fern is still a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.25,0:17:55.48,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll probably always think of her that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.97,0:17:58.46,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.16,0:18:02.22,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We'd better hurry and get those herbs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.54,0:18:07.40,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.56,0:18:34.91,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We should be arriving at the \Nicicle cherry blossom tree soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.91,0:18:39.93,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Is the icicle cherry blossom tree \Nthe last ingredient we need for the medicine?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.93,0:18:43.80,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We'll actually be using the mushrooms \Nthat grow at the base of the tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.45,0:18:59.08,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.08,0:19:01.25,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I wish we could've showed Fern.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.08,0:19:05.45,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It might be my favorite flower \Nthat blooms in winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.94,0:19:09.46,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful. The flowers are poisonous.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.77,0:19:14.72,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, why'd you hold Fern's hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.29,0:19:18.08,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Normally you don't treat her \Nthat much like a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.88,0:19:21.45,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't trying to treat her like a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.21,0:19:25.59,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I simply held her hand because \Nit looked like she was in pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.06,0:19:31.22,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's the only way I know to relieve her pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.72,0:19:36.73,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What should I have done?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.09,0:19:42.36,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I guess you just have to do \Nwhat you want to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.14,0:19:45.73,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,At least, that's what my master did.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.50,0:19:50.77,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,People probably need emotional support.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.90,0:19:55.33,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody dislikes receiving support.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.79,0:20:03.38,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think you're doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.92,0:20:05.66,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,You were moaning in your sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.25,0:20:09.02,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,We feel helpless when we're sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.59,0:20:14.64,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,I lost my mother when I was young, \Nbut she used to hold my hand like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.31,0:20:17.29,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,It's strangely calming.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.29,0:20:19.64,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You mean when you were a child, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.09,0:20:24.13,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,It's not just children who \Nneed emotional support.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.12,0:20:28.11,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't bother you, does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.58,0:20:31.14,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.42,0:20:34.18,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it's not so bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.12,0:20:38.36,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pretty handsome when \NI'm being considerate, aren't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.36,0:20:39.86,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Please just be quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.99,0:20:44.51,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,The medicine is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.69,0:20:51.85,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Fern was probably embarrassed \Nbecause I was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.97,0:20:57.08,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody likes to be seen acting \Nlike a pampered child.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.17,0:21:00.15,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Stark.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.66,0:21:03.67,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll try doing what I want to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.12,0:21:09.58,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,To thank you, I'll hold your hand \Nwhen you get sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.99,0:21:11.88,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Don't. It's embarrassing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.04,0:21:16.88,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's gather some mushrooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.57,0:21:19.24,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Hup.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.58,0:21:22.26,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,They're bigger than I expected! Scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.77,0:21:25.75,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Now we just add the other ingredients...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.03,0:21:29.02,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,And mix very, very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.02,0:21:31.51,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You're like a witch! Really scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.84,0:21:36.03,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Open your mouth, Fern.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.27,0:21:48.57,Default,VILLAGER,0000,0000,0000,,You're good at that. Thanks for the help.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.02,0:21:50.49,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.99,0:21:55.49,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right. You'll feel better soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.04,0:22:00.01,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren, I'm not a child anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.84,0:22:01.88,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.71,0:22:03.98,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.09,0:22:17.28,Default,VILLAGER,0000,0000,0000,,Take care of yourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.23,0:22:21.29,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.81,0:22:23.58,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You're looking a lot better.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.36,0:22:30.28,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I have the two of you and \NMr. Sein's notes to thank for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.28,0:22:35.26,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,The owner of that home was very kind, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.90,0:22:37.80,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.70,0:22:44.03,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Our destination is Äußerst, the city of magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.04,0:22:53.18,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm alright (I'll be alright)
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.18,0:22:56.10,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I hear you (I care about you)
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.10,0:23:01.68,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,The wind teases this hair that's longer now
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.68,0:23:04.12,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,There's meaning in everything
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.62,0:23:07.10,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even the days that came to a halt
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.70,0:23:13.74,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I finally understand,\NI've caught up to you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.74,0:23:17.53,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,See, things that couldn't have been
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.53,0:23:20.43,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Seen if it weren't for these eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.43,0:23:25.10,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Why? They begin to overflow
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.10,0:23:31.33,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I won't ask to see you, so at least
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.33,0:23:37.12,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Let me remember the past, just for today
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.12,0:23:43.13,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,So, if we were to meet again
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.13,0:23:49.01,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,No more hesitations, I'd choose the present
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.07,0:23:53.03,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Anytime, anywhere, yah (wherever you are)
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.03,0:23:57.68,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Anytime, anywhere (smile for me)
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.68,0:24:00.66,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be there (close your eyes,\Nand I'll always be there)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.66,0:24:03.41,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even if there are no absolutes
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.41,0:24:06.48,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I'm always aware of your thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.48,0:24:12.51,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Those tears will be alright,\Ndawn will surely break
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.96,0:24:19.42,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I'm whispering our lullaby\Nfor you to come back home
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.31,0:24:22.81,Default,LERNEN,0000,0000,0000,,Could I take a look at that?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.68,0:24:21.79,DefaultOverlap,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.79,0:24:24.60,DefaultOverlap,ÜBEL,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I'll take a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.08,0:24:24.53,DefaultTop,FALSCH,0000,0000,0000,,This year's test-takers \Nseem rather exceptional.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.81,0:24:24.31,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,You wanna fight, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.31,0:24:26.44,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do this alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.60,0:24:27.23,DefaultOverlap,KRAFT,0000,0000,0000,,You have the eyes of a killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.11,0:24:27.35,DefaultTop,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't call me an old mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.44,0:24:27.25,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Dunno.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.25,0:24:30.58,Default,GENAU,0000,0000,0000,,The first-class mage exam will now begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.57,0:24:30.02,Signs_NextEp,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(229,1)\blur3\t(20,312,\blur0.2)\pos(320,113.5)\c&H000000&\t(312,646,\c&HF6F6F6&)\fsp1.6\t(\fsp1)}Episode 18\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\NFirst-Class Mage Exam